          "type": "assistant",
          "text": "Here's a complete overview of **agent-verdict**:\n\n## What It Is\n\nAn AI agent answer verification library. It takes an agent's output and runs it through a pipeline of evaluation stages to determine if the answer should be trusted or rejected.\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\nUser Interfaces (decorator, CLI, MCP server)\n        ↓\n   VerdictPipeline  →  Stage 1 → Stage 2 → Stage 3 → ... → Final Verdict\n        ↓\n   LLM Providers (Anthropic / OpenAI)\n   + optional offline models (MiniLM, DeBERTa)\n```\n\n**Core flow**: Agent result → `Verdict` object flows through stages sequentially. Any stage can \"drop\" the result (reject it), stopping the pipeline early.\n\n## Key Components\n\n| Component | File | Role |\n|-----------|------|------|\n| **Models** | `models.py` | Pydantic schemas: `Verdict`, `VerdictConfig`, structured outputs |\n| **Pipeline** | `pipeline.py` | Chains stages, handles early termination on drop |\n| **Decorator** | `decorator.py` | `@verdict()` wraps agent functions, auto-evaluates returns |\n| **CLI** | `cli.py` | `evaluate`, `check`, `attack` subcommands; auto-detects provider |\n| **MCP Server** | `mcp_server.py` | 7 tools for Claude Code / Cursor integration |\n| **LLM Base** | `llm/base.py` | ABC with `complete()` + `complete_structured()` (JSON schema) |\n| **Anthropic** | `llm/anthropic.py` | Uses tool_use for structured output (default: claude-sonnet-4-6) |\n| **OpenAI** | `llm/openai.py` | Uses json_schema response format (default: gpt-4o) |\n\n## 7 Evaluation Stages\n\n| # | Stage | LLM Calls | What It Catches |\n|---|-------|-----------|-----------------|\n| 1 | **Confidence** | 1 | Vague/low-quality answers (rates confidence + relevance 0-1) |\n| 2 | **Verification** | 1 | Answers that don't hold up to independent re-derivation |\n| 3 | **Adversarial** | 2 | Plausible but flawed answers (counter-argument → defense) |\n| 4 | **Self-Consistency** | 2N | Unstable answers (re-derives N times, votes on agreement) |\n| 5 | **Semantic Similarity** | 0 | Off-topic answers (MiniLM embeddings, cosine similarity) |\n| 6 | **Entailment** | 0 | Hallucinations/contradictions (DeBERTa NLI classification) |\n| 7 | **Logprob** | 1 | Internally uncertain answers (token log-probabilities, OpenAI only) |\n\nDefault pipeline: stages 1-3 (4 LLM calls). Stages 5-6 use different models, breaking the \"same brain grading itself\" problem.\n\n## Design Highlights\n\n- **Minimal core dependency**: only `pydantic>=2.0`; LLM SDKs and ML models are optional extras\n- **Prompt injection safety**: `sanitize_for_prompt()` escapes XML tags in user data + adds boundary instructions\n- **Structured output**: uses native provider mechanisms (Anthropic tool_use, OpenAI json_schema) rather than parsing free text\n- **Graceful degradation**: embedding/NLI stages fall back to LLM-based evaluation if offline models aren't installed\n- **Three interfaces**: Python decorator, CLI (with stdin pipe support), MCP tools",
